descript.abstract: This polyline feature is used to represent a collection of gravity main lines located within the city limits of Houston, Texas. The gravity main lines transport stormwater runoff between stormwater structures.
descript.purpose: The City of Houston Stormwater Drainage System is designed to manage stormwater flow and enables the disposal directly into major ditches and bayous. Stormwater utility lines are digitized by using the Plan & Profile engineering drawings that come from the following sources: Capital Improvement Projects (CIP), Contractor Participation Drawings (70/30 Projects), Intergovernmental Drawings (ID), and Taps & Meters (T & M.) The above sources provide all the information that is detailed under the stormwater line features. This data may be used for analyzing, maintenance, mapping and planning of city utilities.
descript.supplinf: The stormwater lines are a polyline feature class that is part of a working Telvent Miner & Miner sde geodatabase that is updated daily using the ArcFM Solution software. This geodatabase is replicated several times to different departments within the City of Houston. The replicated data is updated once a week. The City of Houston makes this data available for internal and public use.

procstep.procdesc: Process step one: Digitizing - Technicians sign out a project to be digitized from a maintenance work log, they extract all pertinent tiles in session form, digitize the utility features based on the project requirements, produce check plots, then the session is forwarded to a Quality Assurance/Quality Control (QA/QC ) team member for verification. Process step two: Visual QC - QA/QC staff visually compares the check plots against the source documents to verify that all features were digitized. Process step three: Updates required - If there are any missing data or errors in the digitized features, feedback is provided to the technician and corrections are made to the project. Process step four: Final Logical QC - A QC review program is ran to verify if the attributes were entered correctly. Process step five: Updates Required - If there are any missing data or errors in the digitized features, feedback is provided to the technician and corrections are made to the project. Process step six: The session is then forward to a supervisor who will post the session back to the default sde database. Process step seven: Ready for distribution.
